The '''Shado-Pan Monastery''' is a new dungeon in {{Mists-inline}} Mists of Pandaria.<ref name="blizzcon2011dungeonsraidspanel">{{ref web|work=Official BlizzCon site (US)|url=http://us.battle.net/blizzcon/en/blog/3759858/WoW_Dungeons_and_Raids_Panel-10_21_2011|title=WoW Dungeons and Raids Panel|author=[[Bashiok]]|date=21-Oct 21-2011 4:30 PM PDT}}<br/>&nbsp; &nbsp;{{ref web|work=Official BlizzCon site (EU)|url=http://eu.battle.net/blizzcon/en/blog/3167715/WoW_Dungeons_and_Raids_-22_10_2011|title=WoW Dungeons and Raids|author=[[Bashiok]]|date=22-Oct-2011 01:30 CEST}}</ref> The dungeon is located in the northwest region [[Kun-Lai Summit]], up a winding trail from [[Winter's Blossom]]. A number of [[grummle]] traders are being refused entry by the guards.

The dungeon is home of the [[Shado-Pan]] clan's training grounds, a faction of pandaren who are dedicated to protecting Pandaria. The [[Sha]] are roaming around, looking to destroy the facility.  In fact, the Sha have corrupted the trainees of the Shado-Pan Monastery and it is up to players to free them of their corruption.

